The paper discusses the capacity and generalization of deep convolutional neural networks, which are topics typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on spectral complexity and its limitations also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). However, given the emphasis on deep learning and CNNs, the first five sub-categories are more likely to be relevant.
